= Paul Levi

Levi is a former leader of the KPP who left over their devotion to violence and revolutionary adventurism.

- @building_the_left
- @kpp_cooperation
- @root: Return to main

@building_the_left
title: Building the Left
subtitle: Push the BBWR to the left.
unavailable-subtitle: [? if advisor_action_timer > 0 : [+ advisor_action_timer +] months before next advisor action. ?]
choose-if: advisor_action_timer = 0
on-arrival: advisor_action_timer = 6; left_strength += 10; left_dissent -= 8; reformist_dissent += 3

We have increased the strength of the left faction with the BBWR. This raised concern among the moderate reformists in the party.

@kpp_cooperation
title: Cooperation with the KPP
subtitle: Any cooperation between the parties requires compromise from the KPP as well as the BBWR.
unavailable-subtitle: [? if advisor_action_timer > 0 : [+ advisor_action_timer +] months before next advisor action. ?]
choose-if: advisor_action_timer = 0
on-arrival: advisor_action_timer = 6; left_strength += 5; kpp_relation += 6*(1-dissent); reformist_dissent += 3; communist_coalition += 1 if kpp_cooperation_seen <= 1; kpp_cooperation_seen += 1

Levi attempts to reach out to his former colleagues to dissuade the KPP from their current extreme Stalinist path. Some concessions are extracted.
